rComments: Prof. Bruckel loved all her students so much and you could see the passion she carried for teaching! You'll have homework for every class and although she never checks she calls on students randomly to participate. The final exam was not difficult but extremely long and strenuous

I would really recommend her to everyone who would like to learn something from this course. She is super patient and organizes her lectures clearly. She makes the course interesting by adding extra contents and encourages participation. The homework load is a little heavy, but the tests are not difficult.

Speaks super slowly and its pretty easy to understand her. She is extremely organized and clear in her expectations (with German efficiency). She makes the class interesting and calls out on all the students and encourages participation. I actually enjoy coming to her classes. Highly highly recommend.
Her class is boring, gives students too much homework, and is very strict, does not give students a chance

I enjoyed the class with Angela. She is a very caring Professor and a very sweet lady. Lectures were a little dry. Some days had a hard time staying awake. This class was an easy pass. I don't know how one could fail this class. Grading criteria for final paper poorly made.
Her classes are very homework heavy but she grades pretty easily. She'll love you if you participate.

She's a sweet lady. She tells you what you need to know and how to study. You will be asked questions randomly on the spot so pay attention. Try not to miss class cuz she assigns hw and forgets to post about it on brightspace. Only problem is sometimes she laughs at students when they get the answer wrong, which sucks. Teaching wise, she's good.

Prof. Bruckel is really an amazing prof!!!! My favorite one in the university. She is caring and really wants her students to do well in French. She tries her best to memorize everyone's name. She even consulted a Chinese prof to say my name correctly. :) She is very cute and like to make the class funny. I did really well in her class.
Her teaching methods are a little antiquated, but she doesn't expect much of you. If you have a basic understanding of french, show up and put in your best effort, you'll do great.

The sweetest lady. She tries to make the class interesting, however I feel that she could have done more with the course content. Attendance is mandatory, and homework really only needs to be done to participate in class discussions. Assignments are easy, and she encourages participation.

*FLS 2731 Great course, I enjoyed the real world applications of her teaching. lus I actually saw noticeable improvement in my own french!  Homework not graded and don't try to do it all (cause it's every class) but it's recommended before exams for good practice - helps with exams!

Great course, I enjoyed the real world applications of her teaching. lus I actually saw noticeable improvement in my own french!  Homework not graded and don't try to do it all (cause it's every class) but it's recommended before exams for good practice - helps with exams!
Amazing prof! Learned more in her French class than in any of the other courses I took. I'd definitely take her course again.

This class was super easy for me. The prof was always happy and helpful but she stressed participation and gives lots of little homework assignments pretty much every class but they are very short and easy. Take her class!

I absolutely loved her class! Definitely my favourite this semester. She is so sweet and always encourages everyone to participate. She made fun of our french sometimes, but in a joking way, which just made our class feel closer and more comfortable. I think my French improved a lot and I hope I can have her for another class again!

This professor is so sweet. Although sometimes I felt like there was too much discussion, I know that it was part of the course and she did a decent job at making it at least somewhat interesting. Lots of little assignments but they don't take too long to complete. PS. participation is very important!

By far the best prof you could ask for in a beginner german class. She was really forward in what she expected for assignments and was very easy to talk to when material wasn't clear to you. Hoping to be lucky enough to have her for the rest of my german classes.

Love this prof! She is so sweet & genuinely cares about her students! She's available to answer any questions you have during office hours. There is an above average amount of homework compared to other classes but that's because she teaches languages... if you want to learn a language than lots of work is necessary. I had her for French & German

She's a good prof, you"ll be able to learn german with her if you do the homework & actually want to learn german. There's a lot of student participation so get ready to speak the little german you know every class. Her problems are her classes are often unprepared and she doesn't checks the textbook's materials  before presenting it in class.
Amazing class! I would definitely take a class with her again! Very helpful and resourceful!

She is such an amazing prof! She made learning the language so easy and so fun, and I'm so thankful I had her for my first ever semester of German. Don't skip class, do the homework, and you'll do well. I would definitely try to have her as a prof again.

Participate in class. Even if you didn't do the homework she asks a lot of opinion questions (or make examples), so jump in on those. We did a lot of grammar, even though it wasn't a grammar course, and that made for some boring classes. She's pretty old school, and she knows the French language. You could never tell her first language was German.

She likes to laugh and gives us some pretty funny exercises to improve in this language.  Attendance is mandatory and homework is given after every class, but it actually helped a lot and is a good way to boost marks.  Participation is very important, but if you don't want to participate, she'll call on you anyway.
Great teacher. She is easy to understand and she really cares about her students. I would love to take more language courses with her.

Nice lady, always smiling. A little loopy but it makes the class more interesting. Lots of presentations. Only complaint she's never clear in terms of what we have to do for assignments so make sure you ask her to go over instructions she changes her mind a lot but always tries to be accommodating to everyone. I recommend her class
Great Teacher. Always ready to answer questions. Very upbeat and laughs alot!
One of the best teachers I have ever had she also likes to challenge you but she teaches well and she makes the class a lot of fun
Une des meilleures prof de français que j'ai jamais eu. Communique très bien la matière avec des exemple amusant.

She talks a lot for nothing.  She has a VERY annoting voice.  She doesn't exaplain very much.  She rambles.  The books were fantastic though, and she chose appropriate essay questions that were relatively easy to work on.  As for the exam, it could have been a better topic.
